WEBVTT

00:09.270 --> 00:11.280
[Boyd] <i>Previously on</i>From...

00:11.480 --> 00:12.410
[Sara]
I hear their voices.

00:12.610 --> 00:14.410
They said it was
the only way to go home!

00:14.610 --> 00:16.320
Sara, just tell me
what you did.

00:16.520 --> 00:18.410
[Sara] I left the door open.

00:18.610 --> 00:20.020
[sobbing]

00:23.370 --> 00:24.510
[gasps]

00:24.710 --> 00:26.680
[Tabitha] I saw something
that wasn't there.

00:26.880 --> 00:29.340
- What?
- I saw two children

00:29.540 --> 00:32.200
standing in the middle
of the road, staring at me.

00:33.380 --> 00:34.430
[man on radio]
<i>Is this Jim?</i>

00:34.630 --> 00:36.560
I am not saying
ignore it.

00:36.760 --> 00:40.000
You already got people's hopes
up with your goddamn tower.

00:40.200 --> 00:41.090
All the more
reason that we--

00:41.290 --> 00:43.260
To keep our fucking
mouths shut.

00:43.460 --> 00:44.790
[Sara] What's
about to happen,

00:44.990 --> 00:47.010
it's gonna
save everyone.

00:47.210 --> 00:48.620
[Ethan] Where's my mom?
I want my mom!

00:48.820 --> 00:50.100
[Nathan]
Ethan, run!

00:50.300 --> 00:51.440
[grunts, screams]

00:52.400 --> 00:54.190
[Sara]
Nathan, please!

00:54.390 --> 00:55.710
I spent the entire night
with her,

00:55.910 --> 00:58.800
and that scalpel she used,
she took it from my clinic.

00:59.000 --> 01:00.190
This is not your fault.

01:00.390 --> 01:02.020
[Father] How exactly
are you gonna tell Kenny

01:02.220 --> 01:03.280
that Sara killed his dad?

01:03.480 --> 01:05.500
I did what I had to do!
She was valuable!

01:05.700 --> 01:07.510
She-- she may
still be valuable!

01:07.710 --> 01:10.070
They tore him to pieces,
and you knew!

01:10.270 --> 01:11.160
Kenny, please.

01:11.360 --> 01:13.290
You watch your
own fucking six.

01:14.850 --> 01:17.470
[Jade] There's a symbol
that I keep seeing.

01:17.670 --> 01:18.600
Look at this.

01:19.770 --> 01:21.080
Look. This guy...

01:22.430 --> 01:24.130
he must have been
seeing it, too.

01:24.330 --> 01:25.650
That's you, right?

01:25.850 --> 01:29.090
This could be the key to
getting the hell out of here.

01:29.290 --> 01:31.090
Stay away from me!

01:31.910 --> 01:33.530
Welcome to
your new home.

01:33.730 --> 01:34.610
Hop on up.

01:36.530 --> 01:39.220
Every night,
those things come.

01:40.360 --> 01:42.580
There really
is no way out.

01:47.490 --> 01:52.160
- [knocking]
- [creature screaming]

01:52.360 --> 01:53.370
[knocking]

01:55.280 --> 01:56.370
[knocking]

01:59.240 --> 02:02.640
[knocking]

02:10.520 --> 02:13.560
Hi. Are you
comfortable in there?

02:15.480 --> 02:17.130
You think this is scary?

02:18.480 --> 02:19.400
Huh?

02:21.830 --> 02:23.360
Hiya.

02:23.560 --> 02:25.110
You think
this is scary?

02:25.310 --> 02:27.280
[female creature humming]

02:27.480 --> 02:29.110
What am I
supposed to be?

02:29.310 --> 02:30.550
[humming continues]

02:30.750 --> 02:34.150
Huh? Am I supposed to
be pissing myself? Huh?

02:35.410 --> 02:37.290
Heh. Well, you
can't get in here,

02:37.490 --> 02:40.160
'cause there's a fucking rock
in the fucking window!

02:41.630 --> 02:44.260
Yeah. Yeah, that's real
fucking scary.

02:44.450 --> 02:46.340
I'm not afraid
of you.

02:47.470 --> 02:48.870
You understand me?

02:49.070 --> 02:51.910
[female creature humming]

02:52.110 --> 02:53.520
See ya.

02:58.740 --> 02:59.700
Where you goin'?

03:01.520 --> 03:03.880
Where you goin'?
Hey! [bangs]

03:04.080 --> 03:05.230
Huh? [bangs] Hey!

03:05.430 --> 03:06.630
Huh? [bangs]

03:06.820 --> 03:08.450
- [laughs]
- I'm fucking talking to you.

03:08.650 --> 03:10.450
Don't fucking
walk away from me.

03:17.370 --> 03:19.370
You don't fucking walk
away from me!

03:20.280 --> 03:22.720
[creature screaming]

03:28.510 --> 03:30.650
[creature screaming]

03:30.850 --> 03:31.770
[grunts]

03:32.990 --> 03:36.730
[grunts]

03:41.780 --> 03:42.740
[grunts]

04:06.420 --> 04:08.500
[Jade breathing unsteadily]

04:15.550 --> 04:18.310
[breathing unsteadily]

04:18.510 --> 04:21.260
Oh, God. That motherfucking...

04:23.350 --> 04:24.740
[shouts]

04:26.350 --> 04:28.960
[shouts]

04:29.790 --> 04:33.360
["Que Sera, Sera [Whatever Will
Be, Will Be]" plays]

04:39.540 --> 04:44.380
♪ <i>When I was just a little boy</i>♪

04:44.570 --> 04:46.640
♪ <i>I asked my father</i>♪

04:46.840 --> 04:48.670
♪ <i>"What will I be?"</i>♪

04:50.550 --> 04:52.910
♪ <i>"Will I be handsome?"</i>♪

04:53.100 --> 04:55.340
♪ <i>"Will I be rich?"</i>♪

04:55.540 --> 04:59.390
♪ <i>Here's what he said to me</i>♪

04:59.590 --> 05:02.600
♪ <i>Que sera sera</i>♪

05:03.690 --> 05:07.300
♪ <i>Whatever will be will be</i>♪

05:08.870 --> 05:12.530
♪ <i>The future's not ours to see</i>♪

05:12.730 --> 05:15.660
♪ <i>Que sera sera</i>♪

05:17.660 --> 05:20.750
♪ <i>What will be will be ♪</i>

05:29.890 --> 05:34.900
♪ <i>Now I have</i>
<i>children of my own</i>♪

05:35.100 --> 05:37.380
♪ <i>They ask their father</i>♪

05:37.580 --> 05:40.950
♪ <i>"What will I be?"</i>♪

05:41.150 --> 05:43.480
♪ <i>"Will I be pretty?"</i>♪

05:43.680 --> 05:45.960
♪ <i>"Will I be rich?"</i>♪

05:46.160 --> 05:49.340
♪ <i>I tell them tenderly</i>♪

05:50.040 --> 05:52.780
♪ <i>Que sera sera</i>♪

05:54.220 --> 05:57.660
♪ <i>Whatever will be will be</i>♪

05:58.960 --> 06:02.440
♪ <i>The future's not ours to see</i>♪

06:03.180 --> 06:06.450
♪ <i>Que sera sera</i>♪

06:08.230 --> 06:11.500
♪ <i>What will be will be</i>♪

06:13.540 --> 06:15.510
♪ <i>Que sera sera</i>♪

06:15.710 --> 06:20.770
[song continues to play]

06:30.950 --> 06:34.910
[loud knocking]

06:37.740 --> 06:39.920
[grunts]

06:41.480 --> 06:42.540
Boyd!

06:42.740 --> 06:44.540
Hey! You get
back downstairs.

06:44.740 --> 06:45.840
Stay out of sight.

06:46.040 --> 06:46.970
I'll handle this.

06:48.490 --> 06:49.750
Go!

06:52.100 --> 06:53.980
[knocking]

06:54.180 --> 06:55.410
Coming.

06:56.540 --> 06:57.810
- Where is she?
- Hey, hey, look.

06:58.010 --> 06:59.730
Hey, hey, can
we just calm down?

06:59.930 --> 07:02.430
- Calm down.
- Calm down?

07:02.630 --> 07:03.990
Are you fucking
serious?

07:04.190 --> 07:07.000
There's a lot about this
that you don't understand.

07:07.200 --> 07:09.040
Really? What?

07:09.240 --> 07:10.560
That she hears voices?

07:10.760 --> 07:12.610
That she's important?

07:12.810 --> 07:14.480
Kenny told us.
She's a fucking murderer.

07:14.680 --> 07:16.610
That's what she is.
How could you do this?

07:16.810 --> 07:18.830
She is not going to
hurt anyone!

07:19.030 --> 07:20.840
I don't give a shit what
she's gonna do!

07:21.040 --> 07:22.490
All I care about is what
she's done.

07:22.690 --> 07:24.140
She tried to kill
my fucking kid!

07:24.340 --> 07:26.490
Yes, I know. I know. I know.
I know. I know. I know. I know.

07:26.690 --> 07:28.020
Alright.
So, now what?

07:28.220 --> 07:30.890
We just supposed to pretend
like nothing happened?

07:31.090 --> 07:32.060
What about your rules?

07:32.260 --> 07:33.410
Things have changed.

07:33.610 --> 07:36.200
- How?
- How? Someone put a tower,

07:36.400 --> 07:38.420
a fucking tower,
on Colony House

07:38.620 --> 07:40.030
and told everyone
they were going home!

07:40.230 --> 07:41.990
Now, they're all looking
at me, wondering why

07:42.190 --> 07:44.690
I didn't come back with
all the answers!

07:44.890 --> 07:46.860
We got a busload of people
we don't have resources for,

07:47.060 --> 07:50.690
and a fucking house fell
for no goddamn reason!

07:50.890 --> 07:54.960
So, yeah, if she can help us
figure out what's going on here,

07:55.160 --> 07:58.820
she stays out
of the Box! Period!

08:02.170 --> 08:03.490
- Hey!
- Eh! I told you

08:03.690 --> 08:05.050
to stay
downstairs! Look.

08:05.250 --> 08:06.620
I wanna talk to you.

08:06.820 --> 08:09.010
You need to listen
very fucking carefully.

08:10.790 --> 08:13.670
If you ever come
near my family again,

08:13.870 --> 08:17.490
I swear to God I will
fucking kill you!

08:19.670 --> 08:21.240
Say you understand.

08:21.440 --> 08:22.800
Say you understand!

08:25.330 --> 08:26.630
I do.

08:27.940 --> 08:30.860
Listen. You
have my word--

08:31.060 --> 08:32.900
I don't give a shit
about your word!

08:35.030 --> 08:37.170
- [door opens]
- Jim, listen.

08:37.370 --> 08:41.220
- [door closes]
- Don't even.

08:41.420 --> 08:43.610
[door opens, closes]

08:43.810 --> 08:45.220
Fuck! [bangs]

08:45.420 --> 08:48.050
Goddamn it! [bangs]

08:48.250 --> 08:50.100
[breathing heavily]

08:50.300 --> 08:51.570
Okay.

08:54.830 --> 08:57.930
You lock the door.
You stay inside.

08:58.130 --> 08:59.110
Where are you going?

08:59.310 --> 09:00.540
Colony House.

09:00.740 --> 09:01.940
Gotta talk to Donna.

09:02.140 --> 09:04.810
I want to make sure she
hears this from my mouth.

09:05.010 --> 09:05.930
Boyd!

09:07.800 --> 09:10.850
I shouldn't be here! I...

09:12.940 --> 09:15.560
I'm not strong
enough for this.

09:15.760 --> 09:16.950
That part I can't
help you with,

09:17.150 --> 09:19.080
so you better figure
it out!

09:25.260 --> 09:26.560
[door closes]

09:37.440 --> 09:40.050
[indistinct conversation]

09:41.790 --> 09:46.150
[child shouting
in distance]

09:46.350 --> 09:47.630
[knocking]

09:47.830 --> 09:48.970
[Julie] Ethan.

09:50.280 --> 09:51.640
[knocking]

09:51.840 --> 09:53.640
Ethan, I promise if
you let me in,

09:53.840 --> 09:55.600
it's just me, okay?

09:55.800 --> 09:57.110
There's nobody else
out here.

09:59.460 --> 10:00.870
Ethan, come on.
Please let me in.

10:01.060 --> 10:02.990
Julie, what's
going on?

10:05.990 --> 10:09.260
He heard us last night
talking about Sara.

10:09.460 --> 10:10.740
Now, he won't
come out.

10:15.780 --> 10:17.750
[Tabitha] [knocking]
Ethan? [rattles doorknob]

10:17.950 --> 10:19.580
Honey, I promise no
one's going to hurt you.

10:19.780 --> 10:22.630
[Jim] Yeah. Your mom and I,
we're never gonna let anybody

10:22.830 --> 10:23.880
hurt you.

10:30.020 --> 10:32.900
It's like, uh, with
the Cromenockle?

10:33.100 --> 10:35.890
When she's afraid to
go inside of the cave.

10:49.470 --> 10:50.910
I wanna see her.

10:52.260 --> 10:53.740
I wanna see Sara.

10:57.170 --> 10:59.140
Okay. So, hi.

10:59.340 --> 11:00.880
- [chuckles]
- They're not exactly

11:01.080 --> 11:03.790
chocolate chip, but they're
the best I could do.

11:05.010 --> 11:05.920
Mm.

11:06.920 --> 11:08.240
Here. Careful.
It's hot.

11:08.440 --> 11:09.670
Thank you.

11:09.870 --> 11:12.140
Alright. Ready?
[imitates fanfare]

11:16.890 --> 11:18.380
[laughs]
What are they?

11:18.580 --> 11:21.420
Okay. So, they're these bread
crisps that Tian-Chen makes.

11:21.620 --> 11:25.080
They're, like, a cross
between a cracker and a chip.

11:25.280 --> 11:27.200
They're actually
really good. Okay?

11:35.780 --> 11:36.960
Huh.

11:37.160 --> 11:40.270
Right? Okay. Don't get
crumbs in the bed.

11:40.470 --> 11:41.270
[chuckles]

11:41.470 --> 11:42.700
Thanks.

11:48.920 --> 11:50.710
I have a surprise
for you.

11:50.910 --> 11:52.370
- What?
- [chuckles]

11:52.570 --> 11:55.710
Um... okay.

12:00.410 --> 12:01.930
Close your eyes.

12:03.070 --> 12:04.280
[Marielle
clears throat]

12:14.120 --> 12:15.080
Open them.

12:19.860 --> 12:21.740
- Shut up.
- [chuckles]

12:24.000 --> 12:27.140
How-- how-- how
do even you have this?

12:27.340 --> 12:29.800
Are you kidding? I haven't
gone anywhere without it

12:30.000 --> 12:31.220
since you...

12:32.220 --> 12:33.710
[clears throat]
For a long time,

12:33.910 --> 12:36.460
it still smelled
like you.

12:36.650 --> 12:38.100
Now, it just smells.

12:43.580 --> 12:46.150
I still remember the last time
I saw you wearing it.

12:53.290 --> 12:54.290
Hey.

12:56.120 --> 12:57.080
Hmm?

12:58.290 --> 12:59.350
Where'd you go?

12:59.550 --> 13:00.950
Nowhere. [chuckles]

13:03.470 --> 13:04.780
Kristi, what's wrong?

13:05.870 --> 13:07.750
Nothing.

13:07.950 --> 13:09.000
It's stupid.

13:10.310 --> 13:11.310
Okay.

13:12.660 --> 13:13.920
Tell me anyway.

13:19.010 --> 13:20.880
What if I'm not
the same anymore?

13:22.320 --> 13:26.420
I've just... [chuckles]
...seen things here.

13:26.620 --> 13:28.160
I've had to
do things that--

13:28.360 --> 13:29.190
Hey.

13:32.500 --> 13:33.900
You're still you.

13:34.980 --> 13:36.160
I'm still me.

13:37.550 --> 13:40.170
The rest of it,

13:40.370 --> 13:42.080
we'll figure it
out together.

13:44.170 --> 13:45.080
Hmm?

13:49.910 --> 13:53.140
Every ounce, every
inch, remember?

13:53.340 --> 13:54.350
[chuckles]

14:00.360 --> 14:03.320
[man shouting
indistinctly in distance]

14:03.520 --> 14:05.840
[woman shouting
indistinctly in distance]

14:47.660 --> 14:51.100
[breathes deeply]

15:00.020 --> 15:02.560
[footsteps approaching]

15:02.760 --> 15:03.990
[gasps]

15:07.730 --> 15:09.000
What are you doing?

15:09.200 --> 15:11.040
Sorry. I, uh--

15:11.240 --> 15:12.300
That's my coat.

15:14.000 --> 15:15.480
- No, this is--
- [woman] What's going on?

15:15.680 --> 15:17.090
That girl's here,

15:17.290 --> 15:18.490
the one who killed
her brother.

15:18.690 --> 15:20.440
Please, I just...

15:22.220 --> 15:24.360
- Get the fuck out.
- I don't want any trouble.

15:24.560 --> 15:27.060
You can't have your house back.
Look. She has my coat.

15:27.260 --> 15:28.670
This is my
brother's jacket.

15:28.870 --> 15:30.020
[Paula]
Not anymore it's not.

15:30.220 --> 15:31.500
Put it down and
get the fuck out.

15:31.700 --> 15:33.630
I just
want our things.

15:33.830 --> 15:36.500
There's something
special that I...

15:36.700 --> 15:38.900
[Reggie] The rest of your stuff
is gone. We packed it up.

15:39.100 --> 15:41.150
We-- we gave it to
Kenny's mom for storage.

15:42.760 --> 15:46.380
There was this small ceramic
ornament about this big.

15:46.580 --> 15:47.340
Do you remember?

15:47.540 --> 15:49.000
He just fucking
told you no!

15:49.200 --> 15:52.170
Look. It was creepy
having your stuff here,

15:52.370 --> 15:54.350
and it's really creepy
that you're here right now,

15:54.550 --> 15:58.170
so please just put
the coat down and go away.

15:59.740 --> 16:01.220
- Please.
- Get the fuck out.

16:16.540 --> 16:18.450
Yeah. Okay.

16:20.800 --> 16:22.110
Yeah.

16:24.070 --> 16:25.410
Ah.

16:27.330 --> 16:29.030
Excuse me, bud.
[grunts]

16:35.550 --> 16:36.510
[door closes]

16:37.730 --> 16:39.250
You don't look good.

16:40.690 --> 16:41.600
Tom's dead.

16:42.690 --> 16:44.000
Bar's closed.

16:45.300 --> 16:47.310
- What are you doing?
- Oh, what do you care?

16:49.130 --> 16:50.400
I'm trying to figure
out the symbol

16:50.600 --> 16:53.280
that you refuse to
help me with,

16:53.480 --> 16:55.280
despite the fact that you
clearly know something

16:55.480 --> 16:58.140
- you're not telling me.
- Well, I'll tell you what I can.

17:00.100 --> 17:01.240
- Really?
- Yeah.

17:01.440 --> 17:03.680
First, you have to
do something for me.

17:03.880 --> 17:05.500
Oh.

17:06.110 --> 17:08.160
So, now you need something
from me, you're--

17:08.360 --> 17:10.290
You know what?
First of all, fuck off,

17:10.490 --> 17:13.030
and second
of all, fuck off!

17:16.380 --> 17:17.420
Okay.

17:20.430 --> 17:22.040
Wait!

17:26.480 --> 17:27.790
What do you want?

17:27.990 --> 17:29.170
Mm.

17:32.660 --> 17:34.310
I want you to play.

17:36.750 --> 17:38.450
[door closes]

17:38.650 --> 17:40.630
The fuck is
wrong with you?

17:40.830 --> 17:44.580
If you play, I'll tell you
about the man in the photo.

17:47.840 --> 17:50.460
You tell me about the photo
first. Then I play.

17:51.500 --> 17:53.420
Mm, no.

17:55.240 --> 17:56.600
Just give me
the fuckin' violin.

17:56.800 --> 17:57.680
Not here.

17:58.770 --> 18:00.070
Come.

18:01.210 --> 18:02.340
The fuck?

18:03.600 --> 18:06.250
- Come with me!
- Okay! Alright!

18:07.340 --> 18:09.570
This took me all
fucking night.

18:09.770 --> 18:14.360
[voices chatting
indistinctly in distance]

18:14.560 --> 18:16.660
There's no way I'm letting
him anywhere near that--

18:16.860 --> 18:18.360
Tabby.

18:18.560 --> 18:21.100
How can you even
consider this, Jim?

18:21.790 --> 18:23.100
After Thomas...

18:26.450 --> 18:28.590
Because the doctors
all said

18:28.790 --> 18:31.680
that we should let him
lead sometimes,

18:31.880 --> 18:33.510
and they also said
that we have to let him

18:33.710 --> 18:35.680
work through things
in his own way

18:35.880 --> 18:38.690
and to be there to
support him when he asks.

18:38.890 --> 18:41.330
Anyways, I'll be there,
right there with him.

18:44.640 --> 18:47.260
- I'm coming with you.
- Tabby.

18:47.460 --> 18:50.310
Look. I don't give a shit
what the doctors said.

18:50.510 --> 18:52.090
We're living in
a fucking nightmare,

18:52.290 --> 18:53.610
and that bitch tried
to kill my kid.

18:56.300 --> 18:57.520
Please let me
do this.

19:00.440 --> 19:01.540
Mom?

19:01.740 --> 19:03.830
Hey... Hey.

19:04.490 --> 19:07.280
I remember what
you told me yesterday

19:07.480 --> 19:10.850
about this place,
how scary it is.

19:11.050 --> 19:12.110
Mm-hmm.

19:12.310 --> 19:14.200
When you're on
a quest,

19:14.400 --> 19:17.200
we have to face
the scary things.

19:17.400 --> 19:19.330
That's how you take
their power away.

19:23.980 --> 19:25.330
Yeah.

19:34.390 --> 19:36.310
Stay with
Daddy, okay?

19:36.510 --> 19:38.520
And do exactly
what he tells you.

19:39.480 --> 19:41.570
- Okay.
- Okay.

19:46.050 --> 19:48.800
What were you
fucking doing, Boyd?

19:49.000 --> 19:50.270
[sighs]

19:52.270 --> 19:53.890
By the rules of
this town,

19:54.090 --> 19:55.940
the rules
<i>you</i>created,

19:56.140 --> 19:57.550
that girl should
have gone in the Box

19:57.750 --> 19:58.810
the second
you found her.

19:59.010 --> 20:00.770
Listen. Father Khatri--

20:00.970 --> 20:01.940
Khatri's fucking dead.

20:02.140 --> 20:03.680
Don't you
lay this on him.

20:03.880 --> 20:06.600
You made your
own call here, Boyd.

20:06.800 --> 20:09.600
You told people you
were coming back with answers,

20:09.800 --> 20:11.910
and instead, you came back
with a psychopath

20:12.110 --> 20:14.350
who killed not one
but four people.

20:14.550 --> 20:16.440
And because she's special,
she doesn't have to go

20:16.640 --> 20:19.310
in the Box? Do you
hear what that sounds like?

20:19.510 --> 20:20.610
- She knew things!
- [sighs]

20:20.810 --> 20:22.270
Out in the forest,
she knew things

20:22.470 --> 20:24.270
she couldn't
possibly have known!

20:24.470 --> 20:26.360
Okay. Great.

20:26.560 --> 20:28.270
- So what?
- What do you mean, "So what?"

20:28.470 --> 20:30.800
I mean, we're still
fuckin' here.

20:31.000 --> 20:32.450
Voices or no voices,

20:32.650 --> 20:35.930
do you see a yellow brick
fuckin' road leading us home?

20:36.130 --> 20:37.410
Because I sure don't.

20:37.610 --> 20:40.500
I just see someone who may
have just betrayed

20:40.700 --> 20:43.200
the one thing this place
still has going for it.

20:43.400 --> 20:44.670
And what's that?

20:45.850 --> 20:48.460
Faith. In you.

20:51.330 --> 20:53.470
- You want the truth?
- I mean...

20:53.670 --> 20:58.250
I don't think this has anything
to do with going home.

20:59.510 --> 21:01.520
I think this
is about Abby.

21:03.390 --> 21:05.530
I think you
shot your wife,

21:05.730 --> 21:07.310
and every
morning since,

21:07.510 --> 21:10.400
you wake up wishing
you'd done more,

21:10.600 --> 21:12.840
that you'd
been there for her,

21:13.040 --> 21:15.230
helped her,

21:15.430 --> 21:16.490
fixed her.

21:18.490 --> 21:20.400
But Abby's dead, Boyd.

21:21.450 --> 21:23.540
And Sara's a killer.

21:28.760 --> 21:30.630
You gonna have my
back on this or not?

21:33.420 --> 21:34.770
Okay.

21:35.380 --> 21:37.340
What do
you want, Boyd?

21:37.540 --> 21:40.040
You want my approval?
Y-You want absolution?

21:40.240 --> 21:41.520
'Cause you're
not gonna get it here.

21:41.720 --> 21:43.560
What the hell is that
supposed to mean?

21:44.430 --> 21:46.440
What did
Tian-Chen say?

21:46.640 --> 21:49.480
How does she feel
about Sara being back?

21:50.260 --> 21:52.830
- I haven't--
- Yeah. Well, maybe you should.

21:57.140 --> 22:02.400
[indistinct chatting
in distance]

22:15.070 --> 22:16.420
Sara?

22:22.640 --> 22:24.690
He has something
he wants to say to you.

22:43.010 --> 22:44.710
Everyone thought
you died.

22:46.100 --> 22:47.450
But you didn't.

22:48.880 --> 22:49.890
You lived.

22:51.540 --> 22:52.890
Out in the woods.

22:55.720 --> 22:58.370
Only monsters
live in the woods.

23:01.550 --> 23:03.420
I thought
we were friends.

23:04.990 --> 23:06.380
But we're not.

23:07.560 --> 23:08.900
You're a monster.

23:12.730 --> 23:14.650
And I'm not
afraid of you.

23:18.740 --> 23:19.780
Okay.

23:56.910 --> 23:59.660
- Where are we going?
- It's just a little further.

23:59.860 --> 24:01.840
Listen. You want me to play
something for you, I'll play,

24:02.040 --> 24:04.100
but I'm not gonna wander around
with you all day while you--

24:04.300 --> 24:05.480
It's strange.

24:06.790 --> 24:08.790
The trees,
they're changing.

24:10.620 --> 24:11.880
The fuck does
that mean?

24:24.550 --> 24:27.640
Oh. Well,
this is, uh...

24:41.040 --> 24:42.480
Did you do all this?

24:43.170 --> 24:44.610
After everyone...

24:46.000 --> 24:47.190
Once I was alone,

24:47.380 --> 24:49.540
I-- I didn't want to look
at the cars anymore,

24:49.740 --> 24:53.750
so I put them where I
couldn't see them.

24:54.840 --> 24:57.540
There's more
past the rocks,

24:57.740 --> 24:58.720
a lot more,

24:58.920 --> 25:00.670
but those
were already here.

25:02.320 --> 25:03.710
Come on.

25:05.150 --> 25:08.470
I'm sorry about
what happened yesterday.

25:08.670 --> 25:10.470
I don't like when
people touch my things,

25:10.670 --> 25:12.770
and when I
heard you play...

25:13.900 --> 25:17.910
Uh, sometimes,
I get angry,

25:18.110 --> 25:19.030
and I'm sorry.

25:22.340 --> 25:23.690
Okay.

25:30.260 --> 25:31.530
Here.

25:33.090 --> 25:35.230
- Here what?
- This is where you play.

25:35.430 --> 25:36.880
Oh, thank God. Here.

25:39.660 --> 25:41.750
What do you, uh--
What do you wanna hear?

25:43.280 --> 25:45.110
Play the one
about the star.

25:45.310 --> 25:46.540
The what?

25:48.630 --> 25:50.070
Twinkling star.

25:57.730 --> 25:59.120
This was
your mother's car.

26:05.650 --> 26:08.690
She used to play
it when I was afraid.

26:09.820 --> 26:13.050
And I'd sit up here,
just like this,

26:13.250 --> 26:14.740
and she'd play.

26:15.960 --> 26:17.540
At night,
when we hid,

26:17.740 --> 26:18.970
when I heard
the people screaming,

26:19.170 --> 26:22.840
she'd tell me to think
about the twinkling stars.

26:24.970 --> 26:28.580
And then... I wouldn't
be afraid anymore.

26:29.930 --> 26:31.110
Do you
know that song?

26:33.760 --> 26:37.590
Yeah. Uh... I know it.

26:45.730 --> 26:50.820
[plays "Twinkle,
Twinkle, Little Star"]

27:07.750 --> 27:12.890
[Jade continues
to play]

27:19.760 --> 27:24.900
[Jade continues
to play]

27:31.780 --> 27:36.910
[Jade continues
to play]

27:37.780 --> 27:42.920
[Jade continues
to play]

27:51.970 --> 27:54.100
[Jade finishes song]

28:00.890 --> 28:03.080
Oh. Uh, I'm sorry.

28:03.280 --> 28:04.200
I didn't mean to...

28:11.990 --> 28:13.860
I didn't think
anyone would be here.

28:15.210 --> 28:16.210
It's okay.

28:18.390 --> 28:19.820
Plenty of room.

28:39.450 --> 28:40.710
Were you on the bus?

28:42.240 --> 28:43.150
Yeah.

28:45.810 --> 28:46.980
I'm sorry.

28:57.600 --> 28:59.250
Have you been
here long?

29:00.260 --> 29:01.340
A couple months.

29:03.820 --> 29:05.740
Feels like
much longer.

29:08.130 --> 29:10.440
Do you live
here in town?

29:11.180 --> 29:14.450
I mean, obviously,
you-- you live in town.

29:14.650 --> 29:15.920
I just...

29:17.450 --> 29:20.880
I hadn't seen you
up at the Colony House.

29:22.150 --> 29:23.890
I would've
noticed you.

29:25.450 --> 29:27.760
I, um...

29:30.020 --> 29:32.040
I guess right now,
I live here.

29:32.230 --> 29:35.730
I figured a priest
would live here

29:35.930 --> 29:37.170
or something.

29:37.370 --> 29:38.380
There used to be.

29:40.860 --> 29:41.990
Oh.

29:47.260 --> 29:49.440
I go every Sunday with
my grandma.

29:49.640 --> 29:51.920
Uh, to church,
I mean.

29:53.130 --> 29:54.830
As long as
I can remember.

29:57.310 --> 30:00.060
Is that where you were going
when you were on the bus?

30:00.260 --> 30:02.200
To see
your grandmother?

30:02.400 --> 30:06.230
Yeah. She... uh...

30:10.060 --> 30:12.070
I go see her
every weekend.

30:13.370 --> 30:15.170
I was never
all that religious,

30:15.360 --> 30:19.210
but... it always made
her happy,

30:19.410 --> 30:21.390
you know, me going to
church with her,

30:21.590 --> 30:25.090
and afterwards, we'd spend
the afternoon sitting outside,

30:25.290 --> 30:28.430
making these little
crochet owls.

30:29.520 --> 30:30.820
Really?

30:32.040 --> 30:35.970
It was always
an owl.

30:36.170 --> 30:38.360
And she has
hundreds of 'em.

30:38.560 --> 30:40.920
Uh, she would give them
to every person that she met.

30:41.970 --> 30:43.450
And I-- I
would tell her,

30:43.650 --> 30:48.110
"Grandma, maybe we could try to
switch it up a little bit.

30:48.310 --> 30:51.850
Maybe try a dog or
a bunny or something."

30:52.670 --> 30:54.510
But she'd tell me,

30:54.710 --> 30:57.420
"Elgin, I like
what I like,

30:57.620 --> 30:59.370
and I like owls."

31:00.420 --> 31:02.330
So we made owls.

31:05.680 --> 31:08.350
You must think
I'm really cool.

31:08.550 --> 31:09.380
[chuckles]

31:13.340 --> 31:16.260
I was kind of a dork
when I was a kid.

31:17.570 --> 31:19.140
My brother and I,

31:19.340 --> 31:23.930
we used to collect these little
ceramic Christmas ornaments

31:24.130 --> 31:25.400
from the dollar store
in town.

31:26.580 --> 31:28.110
We'd save up
all our money.

31:28.310 --> 31:31.020
We'd go every chance we got,
like, all year round.

31:31.220 --> 31:33.020
We wouldn't even wait
for Christmas.

31:34.580 --> 31:37.030
And then we'd get home,
and we would paint them

31:37.230 --> 31:40.110
with all
these crazy colors.

31:41.160 --> 31:42.950
We had so many at
one point,

31:43.150 --> 31:45.040
we could've decorated
a hundred trees

31:45.240 --> 31:47.210
and still had
some left over.

31:47.410 --> 31:50.250
Nathan's always looked
a lot better than mine.

31:53.430 --> 31:55.130
I thought
they were all gone.

31:57.390 --> 31:58.390
Turns out...

32:01.180 --> 32:05.010
Nathan kept one with him
all these years.

32:06.480 --> 32:09.970
He said it reminded him of
a time when things were...

32:12.750 --> 32:15.100
Is he here now?

32:16.100 --> 32:17.280
Your brother?

32:20.370 --> 32:21.330
He was.

32:30.770 --> 32:32.080
What happened
to the ornament?

32:32.280 --> 32:36.650
It's here...
somewhere. I just...

32:36.850 --> 32:40.700
I think the person who has
it won't wanna give it back.

32:40.900 --> 32:42.230
Hey.

32:42.420 --> 32:45.480
You need some muscle,
I'm happy to talk to 'em.

32:48.790 --> 32:50.090
You're sweet.

32:52.230 --> 32:55.190
How come you don't stay up
at the Colony House?

32:55.390 --> 32:58.410
I mean, the people up there seem
friendly, for the most part.

32:59.580 --> 33:03.410
No reason to be hanging
around an old, musty church.

33:05.410 --> 33:08.290
It always seemed like
such a nice idea...

33:11.460 --> 33:13.120
that no matter what
you did...

33:14.510 --> 33:16.510
if you
were truly sorry...

33:18.210 --> 33:19.510
then God would
forgive you.

33:21.390 --> 33:23.040
Do you
think that's true?

33:24.080 --> 33:26.270
That part
always seemed

33:26.470 --> 33:29.610
a bit like wishful
thinking to me.

33:31.270 --> 33:35.400
Why? Did you do something
that needs forgiving?

33:39.750 --> 33:41.280
I killed my brother.

33:47.460 --> 33:48.630
But it was
an accident.

33:51.150 --> 33:52.290
Right?

33:53.850 --> 33:55.730
- I mean, you wouldn't--
- You'll find out everything

33:55.930 --> 33:57.200
soon enough.

34:00.770 --> 34:05.390
Uh... maybe
I should, uh...

34:06.430 --> 34:07.390
Uh...

34:10.430 --> 34:12.440
It was really nice to
meet you, Elgin.

34:17.880 --> 34:20.110
Yeah.

34:20.310 --> 34:22.060
It was nice, uh...

34:24.880 --> 34:26.280
nice meeting
you, too.

34:43.690 --> 34:44.640
How did it go?

34:45.770 --> 34:47.650
You okay?

34:47.850 --> 34:49.130
I'm not afraid
anymore.

34:49.330 --> 34:52.430
Oh, baby,
I'm so proud of you.

34:53.780 --> 34:56.490
[Julie]
Hey. Nice going.

34:56.690 --> 34:58.490
Can you come help me
peel some potatoes for dinner?

34:58.690 --> 34:59.840
I don't wanna peel
potatoes.

35:00.040 --> 35:01.100
Okay. Neither do I.

35:01.300 --> 35:02.500
- Go on.
- Let's go.

35:02.700 --> 35:03.570
Come on.

35:09.710 --> 35:11.160
How did he do?

35:11.360 --> 35:14.630
- He did great.
- Yeah? Oh, God.

35:16.980 --> 35:18.560
Life lessons
from the Cromenockle.

35:18.750 --> 35:20.460
[kisses] Who would
have thought?

35:45.530 --> 35:46.530
[gasps]

35:53.230 --> 35:54.360
I'm sorry.

35:56.540 --> 35:58.160
I shouldn't
have come here.

35:58.360 --> 35:59.730
[speaks Cantonese]

35:59.930 --> 36:01.150
Wait.

36:08.640 --> 36:10.210
You take from me.

36:15.300 --> 36:17.260
You take him from me.

36:19.260 --> 36:20.390
Yes.

36:21.870 --> 36:23.700
I take care of you.

36:25.870 --> 36:27.180
But you...

36:28.920 --> 36:32.580
you put hate
inside me.

36:37.320 --> 36:38.760
I know why you come.

36:39.890 --> 36:41.190
You wait.

37:06.390 --> 37:07.520
You take and go.

37:08.610 --> 37:10.750
You never come
here, this place.

37:11.830 --> 37:13.400
You never
come again.

37:16.750 --> 37:17.750
[bangs]

37:20.320 --> 37:23.850
[clatters]

37:24.050 --> 37:26.630
[Tian-Chen sobbing]

37:28.980 --> 37:32.550
[sobbing continues]

37:36.420 --> 37:38.520
- Are you kidding me?
- Kenny, I just--

37:38.720 --> 37:39.650
- Hey!
- Kenny, I--

37:39.850 --> 37:41.350
- What? What?
- I wasn't doing anything.

37:41.550 --> 37:42.830
You weren't doing
anything what? Give me that.

37:43.030 --> 37:44.660
- Kenny, please. Kenny, please!
- What the fuck is in it?

37:44.860 --> 37:46.880
Give me that. [grunts]
Your stuff? Huh?

37:47.080 --> 37:48.710
This is
your stuff, right?

37:48.900 --> 37:49.660
Is this Nathan's?

37:49.860 --> 37:50.970
What's that?
Give me that.

37:51.170 --> 37:53.840
- Stop. Stop! No! Please!
- Give me it. Give me it.

37:54.040 --> 37:55.230
What is this?

37:55.430 --> 37:56.410
- This important to you? Huh?
- Kenny.

37:56.610 --> 37:57.800
- This is meaningful?
- Kenny, please.

37:58.000 --> 37:59.500
- This mean a lot to you?
- Don't, please.

37:59.700 --> 38:01.620
- Fuck you!
- [onlookers] Oh.

38:04.450 --> 38:07.640
Hey. Hey.
Look. Listen.

38:07.840 --> 38:08.720
Look at me!

38:09.890 --> 38:14.380
I don't care what Boyd says,
and I don't give a shit

38:14.580 --> 38:16.040
how fucking special you
think you are.

38:16.240 --> 38:20.520
You ever come near my
mom again, and I swear to God

38:20.720 --> 38:23.560
I will drag your fucking psycho
ass into that Box myself.

38:24.470 --> 38:25.690
Do you
understand me?

38:27.600 --> 38:29.270
Do you understand?

38:29.470 --> 38:30.270
Yes.

38:30.470 --> 38:33.830
[crying]

38:35.530 --> 38:37.660
[onlookers murmur
indistinctly]

38:46.010 --> 38:47.720
[door opens]

38:47.920 --> 38:53.330
[onlookers murmur
indistinctly]

39:10.130 --> 39:11.350
Can I see?

39:11.550 --> 39:12.520
Hold on.

39:13.560 --> 39:14.870
Almost done.

39:18.530 --> 39:20.880
There we go.

39:21.440 --> 39:23.670
- Can I see?
- [chuckles]

39:23.870 --> 39:28.360
Keep in mind... I'm a
little out of practice.

39:29.840 --> 39:31.630
Ooh!

39:31.830 --> 39:33.580
- I think we did okay.
- [gasps]

39:39.980 --> 39:41.510
- I love it.
- Yeah?

39:41.710 --> 39:42.900
- [door opens]
- Come here.

39:44.990 --> 39:46.870
- I look like me again.
- [chuckles]

39:47.070 --> 39:47.950
[door closes]

39:50.030 --> 39:52.700
Oh, excuse me. Uh...

39:52.900 --> 39:54.130
Hi.

39:54.330 --> 39:57.490
Hi. I-- I was
looking for Kristi.

39:57.690 --> 39:59.790
Yeah. That's me. Hi.

39:59.990 --> 40:01.620
Sorry. I didn't
mean to interrupt.

40:01.820 --> 40:05.150
Oh, no. It's fine. [laughs]
How can I help you?

40:05.350 --> 40:07.530
Well, uh...
[unzips pack]

40:08.880 --> 40:11.010
...since you're
the resident Quincy...

40:15.500 --> 40:17.020
...I was hoping I
could give you this.

40:19.930 --> 40:22.500
Uh, why are you carrying around
liquid morphine?

40:28.600 --> 40:32.560
Mm. Um, when were
you diagnosed?

40:33.510 --> 40:35.570
About a month ago.

40:35.770 --> 40:37.660
I figure that by
the time I need that,

40:37.860 --> 40:41.830
I probably won't be
in any shape to...

40:42.030 --> 40:43.490
[sighs]

40:43.690 --> 40:44.840
I'll take care
of it, okay?

40:45.040 --> 40:46.440
Thank you.

40:47.270 --> 40:48.670
Look what I did.

40:48.870 --> 40:50.970
Ruined such a
nice afternoon.

40:51.170 --> 40:53.060
[laughs]

40:53.260 --> 40:55.070
I'll let you
get back to it.

40:55.260 --> 40:57.850
Oh, well, you're better
off in here, anyway.

40:58.050 --> 41:00.200
Oh, there's lots
of hubbub flying around

41:00.400 --> 41:02.800
now that that
Sara girl's back.

41:04.070 --> 41:05.460
I'm sorry. What?

41:07.330 --> 41:09.070
Kristi, where are
you going?

41:09.680 --> 41:11.780
- Baby, stop!
- No! I have to--

41:11.980 --> 41:13.040
- Stop!
- I have to go!

41:13.240 --> 41:15.520
Hey, just
talk to me!

41:15.720 --> 41:17.170
Hey! Talk to me!

41:17.370 --> 41:19.440
What is going on?

41:19.640 --> 41:21.870
You're not
going anywhere, okay?

41:22.070 --> 41:23.440
Not like this.

41:23.640 --> 41:24.920
Who is Sara?

41:25.120 --> 41:26.660
She killed somebody,

41:26.860 --> 41:29.050
and then she tried to kill
a little boy because I...

41:32.270 --> 41:34.060
We were talking one night.
She was at the clinic,

41:34.260 --> 41:37.800
and... and she asked me what I
would do to see you again.

41:38.000 --> 41:39.890
If it was something bad,
would it be worth it?

41:40.090 --> 41:40.940
And I said yes.

41:41.140 --> 41:42.200
I don't...

41:42.400 --> 41:43.550
I gave
her permission,

41:43.750 --> 41:45.800
and then the next day,
she-- Fuck.

41:48.680 --> 41:50.600
I just wanted to see
you again so badly that I--

41:50.800 --> 41:52.470
I wasn't even
listening to the question,

41:52.670 --> 41:53.910
and now, you're here,
and I'm wondering

41:54.110 --> 41:56.080
if that's my fault,
too. And I just...

41:56.280 --> 41:57.910
No. I just feel like all
I've been doing lately is

41:58.110 --> 42:00.860
- hurting people, and I just--
- No. Hey.

42:02.730 --> 42:04.960
This is
not your fault.

42:05.160 --> 42:07.220
I am here.

42:07.420 --> 42:08.570
Okay?

42:08.770 --> 42:09.870
We're together.

42:14.140 --> 42:15.140
Come inside.

42:18.010 --> 42:18.920
Come inside.

42:28.410 --> 42:30.540
His name
was Christopher.

42:31.370 --> 42:32.680
Christopher.

42:35.370 --> 42:36.690
Come with me.

42:36.890 --> 42:38.260
What?
No. Come on.

42:38.450 --> 42:39.870
It's right over here.

42:40.070 --> 42:40.940
[sighs]

42:49.260 --> 42:50.950
This was his car.

42:58.090 --> 43:01.280
He seemed nice at first,
'cause he made people laugh.

43:01.480 --> 43:03.970
That-- that wasn't an easy
thing to do back then.

43:05.360 --> 43:06.800
People liked him.

43:09.020 --> 43:10.020
And then?

43:14.020 --> 43:15.600
Then he changed.

43:15.800 --> 43:18.160
- Changed how?
- I-- I don't...

43:18.360 --> 43:20.250
I don't like this.
Uh, we should go back.

43:20.450 --> 43:22.990
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

43:24.470 --> 43:25.780
- But we had a deal.
- Mm.

43:25.980 --> 43:28.310
Right? I played your
song. I held up my end.

43:28.500 --> 43:29.650
You don't understand.

43:29.850 --> 43:31.310
You shouldn't be asking
these questions.

43:31.510 --> 43:32.610
Why? Why? Why?

43:32.810 --> 43:34.000
- Mm.
- Huh?

43:35.870 --> 43:38.840
Look. I haven't had
a good night's sleep

43:39.040 --> 43:41.670
since I fucking got here,
and I'm-- and I'm seeing things,

43:41.870 --> 43:43.760
things that are scaring
the shit out of me.

43:43.960 --> 43:47.110
And it's-- and it's all
because of this, right here!

43:47.310 --> 43:49.890
And whoever this Christopher
guy was, he saw it, too!

43:50.090 --> 43:51.020
He saw it.
He obsessed over it.

43:51.220 --> 43:52.810
He drew it a thousand
fucking times.

43:53.010 --> 43:55.680
So you playing your whole weird,
creepy mystery man routine,

43:55.880 --> 43:56.990
it's not exactly
helping me feel any better!

43:57.190 --> 43:58.680
When did he
start seeing the symbol?

43:58.880 --> 44:00.030
- I don't know.
