48:10.610 --> 48:13.500
[sighs] Look. I don't wanna
do this right now, Jim.

48:13.700 --> 48:15.370
I'm not here to argue.

48:15.570 --> 48:19.020
I mean, I don't agree
with what you did, but...

48:20.240 --> 48:21.550
...but I looked
at that girl today,

48:21.750 --> 48:23.640
and I didn't see
a psychopath.

48:23.840 --> 48:24.990
I didn't see
a vicious killer.

48:25.190 --> 48:27.290
I saw a broken kid.

48:29.210 --> 48:31.160
And I'm looking
around, and...

48:31.990 --> 48:35.480
I'm seeing a lot of people
pushed to their edge.

48:35.680 --> 48:37.400
Okay.

48:37.600 --> 48:40.570
You ever wonder if
maybe that's the point?

48:40.770 --> 48:42.140
What are you
talking about?

48:42.340 --> 48:44.050
We heard a voice
on the radio.

48:45.220 --> 48:47.060
Yeah. Me and Donna,

48:47.260 --> 48:49.280
right as the storm
was coming in,

48:49.480 --> 48:51.500
and whoever it was,
he knew my name,

48:51.700 --> 48:53.330
knew what my wife was
doing in the house,

48:53.530 --> 48:56.230
in the basement
of our house.

48:57.450 --> 49:00.160
And I thought
maybe I was crazy.

49:00.360 --> 49:01.380
I think people
are watching us.

49:01.580 --> 49:04.340
- I think people are listening.
- Jim--

49:04.540 --> 49:06.300
[Jim] Now, there
are experiments like this

49:06.490 --> 49:09.080
